<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8">
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
<title>Youri Suh / 서유리</title>
<link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com">
<link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin>
<link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=EB+Garamond:ital,wght@0,400;0,500;1,400&family=Noto+Serif+KR:wght@300;400&family=Courier+Prime:ital@0;1&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
<style>
  *, *::before, *::after { box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0; padding: 0; }

  :root {
    --bg: #f4f2ed;
    --fg: #1a1a18;
    --fg-muted: #888580;
    --line: #d8d4cc;
    --sidebar-w: 210px;
    --sans: 'EB Garamond', Georgia, serif;
    --sans-kr: 'Noto Serif KR', serif;
    --mono: 'Courier Prime', monospace;
  }

  html { font-size: 15px; scroll-behavior: smooth; }

  body {
    background: var(--bg);
    color: var(--fg);
    font-family: var(--sans);
    min-height: 100vh;
    display: flex;
    opacity: 0;
    animation: fadeIn 0.5s ease forwards;
  }
  @keyframes fadeIn { to { opacity: 1; } }

  /* ── SIDEBAR ── */
  aside {
    position: fixed;
    top: 0; left: 0; bottom: 0;
    width: var(--sidebar-w);
    padding: 1.8rem 1.6rem 2rem;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    border-right: 1px solid var(--line);
    background: var(--bg);
    z-index: 10;
    overflow-y: auto;
  }

  /* ── CREATURE ── */
  .creature-wrap {
    width: 100%;
    margin-bottom: 1.8rem;
    cursor: pointer;
    position: relative;
    height: 80px;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
  }
  .creature-frame {
    position: absolute;
    top: 0; left: 0;
    width: 100%;
    height: 80px;
    object-fit: contain;
    object-position: left center;
    opacity: 0;
    transition: opacity 0.05s;
    filter: invert(0);
  }
  .creature-frame.visible { opacity: 1; }

  /* ── NAV ── */
  .nav-group { margin-bottom: 1.4rem; }
  .nav-group-label {
    font-family: var(--mono);
    font-size: 0.6rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.14em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--fg-muted);
    margin-bottom: 0.35rem;
    display: block;
    font-weight: 300;
  }

  nav a {
    display: block;
    font-family: var(--sans);
    font-size: 0.82rem;
    font-weight: 400;
    color: var(--fg-muted);
    text-decoration: none;
    line-height: 1.8;
    transition: color 0.15s;
    cursor: pointer;
    letter-spacing: 0.01em;
  }
  nav a:hover { color: var(--fg); }
  nav a.active { color: var(--fg); font-weight: 500; }

  .sidebar-bottom {
    margin-top: auto;
    padding-top: 1.2rem;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--line);
  }
  .lang-toggle {
    font-family: var(--mono);
    font-size: 0.6rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    color: var(--fg-muted);
    cursor: pointer;
    border: none;
    background: none;
    padding: 0;
    display: block;
    margin-bottom: 0.6rem;
    font-weight: 300;
  }
  .lang-toggle:hover { color: var(--fg); }
  .sidebar-contact a {
    display: block;
    font-family: var(--mono);
    font-size: 0.62rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.04em;
    color: var(--fg-muted);
    text-decoration: none;
    line-height: 1.9;
    font-weight: 300;
  }
  .sidebar-contact a:hover { color: var(--fg); }

  /* ── MAIN ── */
  main {
    margin-left: var(--sidebar-w);
    flex: 1;
    padding: 3.2rem 3.5rem 6rem 4rem;
    max-width: 820px;
  }

  /* ── SECTIONS ── */
  section { display: none; }
  section.active { display: block; animation: sectionIn 0.35s ease forwards; }
  @keyframes sectionIn { from { opacity: 0; transform: translateY(6px); } to { opacity: 1; transform: translateY(0); } }

  /* ── ABOUT ── */
  #about h1 {
    font-size: clamp(1.6rem, 3vw, 2.4rem);
    font-weight: 300;
    line-height: 1.2;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    margin-bottom: 0.2rem;
  }
  #about h1 .kr {
    display: block;
    font-family: var(--sans-kr);
    font-size: clamp(0.85rem, 1.8vw, 1.1rem);
    font-weight: 300;
    color: var(--fg-muted);
    margin-top: 0.2rem;
    letter-spacing: 0;
  }
  .divider { width: 32px; height: 1px; background: var(--line); margin: 1.8rem 0; }
  .statement {
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    line-height: 1.95;
    color: #2e2e2c;
    max-width: 560px;
    font-weight: 300;
  }
  .statement.kr {
    font-family: var(--sans-kr);
    font-size: 0.88rem;
    line-height: 2.1;
    font-weight: 300;
  }

  /* ── SECTION TITLES ── */
  .section-title {
    font-size: clamp(1.3rem, 2.5vw, 1.8rem);
    font-weight: 300;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    margin-bottom: 0.3rem;
  }
  .section-sub {
    font-family: var(--mono);
    font-size: 0.64rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    color: var(--fg-muted);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    margin-bottom: 2.4rem;
    display: block;
    font-weight: 300;
  }

  /* ── WMLALIVE intro ── */
  .wml-intro {
    font-size: 0.92rem;
    line-height: 1.95;
    color: #2e2e2c;
    max-width: 540px;
    margin-bottom: 2.8rem;
    border-left: 2px solid var(--line);
    padding-left: 1.3rem;
    font-weight: 300;
  }
  .wml-intro.kr {
    font-family: var(--sans-kr);
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    font-weight: 300;
    line-height: 2.1;
  }

  /* ── PROJECT CARDS ── */
  .project-card {
    border-top: 1px solid var(--line);
    padding: 1.6rem 0;
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 90px 1fr;
    gap: 0 1.8rem;
  }
  .project-card:last-child { border-bottom: 1px solid var(--line); }
  .project-year {
    font-family: var(--mono);
    font-size: 0.65rem;
    color: var(--fg-muted);
    letter-spacing: 0.06em;
    padding-top: 0.12rem;
    font-weight: 300;
  }
  .project-title {
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    margin-bottom: 0.3rem;
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
  }
  .project-meta {
    font-family: var(--mono);
    font-size: 0.62rem;
    color: var(--fg-muted);
    letter-spacing: 0.03em;
    margin-bottom: 0.55rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
    font-weight: 300;
  }
  .project-desc {
    font-size: 0.84rem;
    line-height: 1.85;
    color: #4a4a48;
    max-width: 440px;
    font-weight: 300;
  }
  .project-desc.kr {
    font-family: var(--sans-kr);
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    font-weight: 300;
    line-height: 2;
  }
  .project-link {
    display: inline-block;
    margin-top: 0.75rem;
    font-family: var(--mono);
    font-size: 0.62rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--fg-muted);
    text-decoration: none;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--line);
    padding-bottom: 1px;
    transition: color 0.2s, border-color 0.2s;
    font-weight: 300;
  }
  .project-link:hover { color: var(--fg); border-color: var(--fg); }

  .img-placeholder {
    margin-top: 0.9rem;
    width: 100%;
    max-width: 360px;
    aspect-ratio: 4/3;
    background: var(--line);
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    font-family: var(--mono);
    font-size: 0.6rem;
    color: var(--fg-muted);
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    font-weight: 300;
  }

  /* ── CV ── */
  .cv-block { margin-bottom: 2.5rem; }
  .cv-block-title {
    font-family: var(--mono);
    font-size: 0.62rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.14em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--fg-muted);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--line);
    padding-bottom: 0.45rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.9rem;
    font-weight: 300;
  }
  .cv-row {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 46px 1fr;
    gap: 0 1.4rem;
    padding: 0.48rem 0;
    border-bottom: 1px solid #e4e0d8;
  }
  .cv-row:last-child { border-bottom: none; }
  .cv-year {
    font-family: var(--mono);
    font-size: 0.65rem;
    color: var(--fg-muted);
    padding-top: 0.1rem;
    font-weight: 300;
  }
  .cv-title-text { font-size: 0.88rem; font-weight: 400; line-height: 1.4; }
  .cv-detail {
    font-family: var(--mono);
    font-size: 0.62rem;
    color: var(--fg-muted);
    letter-spacing: 0.03em;
    margin-top: 0.15rem;
    font-weight: 300;
  }

  /* ── ARCHIVE GRID ── */
  .archive-note {
    font-family: var(--mono);
    font-size: 0.64rem;
    color: var(--fg-muted);
    letter-spacing: 0.06em;
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
    display: block;
    font-weight: 300;
  }

  .archive-filter {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 0.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 1.8rem;
  }
  .filter-btn {
    font-family: var(--mono);
    font-size: 0.6rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    border: 1px solid var(--line);
    background: none;
    color: var(--fg-muted);
    padding: 0.3rem 0.7rem;
    cursor: pointer;
    transition: all 0.15s;
    font-weight: 300;
  }
  .filter-btn:hover, .filter-btn.active {
    background: var(--fg);
    color: var(--bg);
    border-color: var(--fg);
  }

  .archive-photo-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    gap: 3px;
  }
  .archive-photo-item {
    aspect-ratio: 1;
    background: var(--line);
    position: relative;
    overflow: hidden;
    cursor: pointer;
  }
  .archive-photo-item:hover .archive-overlay { opacity: 1; }
  .archive-overlay {
    position: absolute;
    inset: 0;
    background: rgba(26,26,24,0.82);
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    opacity: 0;
    transition: opacity 0.2s;
    padding: 0.8rem;
    text-align: center;
  }
  .archive-overlay-cat {
    font-family: var(--mono);
    font-size: 0.55rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.12em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: rgba(255,255,255,0.6);
    margin-bottom: 0.3rem;
    font-weight: 300;
  }
  .archive-overlay-name {
    font-size: 0.78rem;
    font-weight: 400;
    color: #fff;
    line-height: 1.3;
  }
  .archive-overlay-name .kr {
    display: block;
    font-family: var(--sans-kr);
    font-size: 0.7rem;
    font-weight: 300;
    color: rgba(255,255,255,0.7);
    margin-top: 0.15rem;
  }
  .archive-photo-item img {
    width: 100%; height: 100%;
    object-fit: cover;
    display: block;
  }
  /* placeholder color per category */
  .archive-photo-item[data-cat="conceptual"] { background: #c8c4bc; }
  .archive-photo-item[data-cat="book"] { background: #d4cfc6; }
  .archive-photo-item[data-cat="illustration"] { background: #dedad2; }
  .archive-photo-item[data-cat="photo"] { background: #c4c0b8; }

  /* hidden */
  .hidden { display: none !important; }

  /* ── RESPONSIVE ── */
  @media (max-width: 680px) {
    aside {
      position: static;
      width: 100%;
      border-right: none;
      border-bottom: 1px solid var(--line);
      flex-direction: row;
      flex-wrap: wrap;
      padding: 1rem 1.2rem;
      gap: 0.6rem;
      align-items: center;
    }
    .creature-wrap { height: 48px; width: 80px; margin-bottom: 0; flex-shrink: 0; }
    .creature-frame { height: 48px; }
    .nav-group { margin-bottom: 0; }
    .nav-group-label { display: none; }
    nav a { display: inline; margin-right: 0.8rem; font-size: 0.78rem; }
    .sidebar-bottom { border: none; padding: 0; margin: 0; }
    main { margin-left: 0; padding: 2rem 1.2rem 4rem; }
    .project-card { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .project-year { margin-bottom: 0.25rem; }
    .archive-photo-grid { grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr); }
  }
</style>
</head>
<body>

<aside>
  <!-- Creature blink animation -->
  <div class="creature-wrap" onclick="showSection('about')" title="Youri Suh / 서유리">
    <img class="creature-frame visible" id="cf1" src="data:image/png;base64," alt="creature eye open">
    <img class="creature-frame" id="cf2" src="data:image/png;base64," alt="creature half blink">
    <img class="creature-frame" id="cf3" src="data:image/png;base64," alt="creature eyes closed">
  </div>

  <nav>
    <div class="nav-group">
      <span class="nav-group-label">Projects</span>
      <a href="#" onclick="showSection('wmlalive')" data-section="wmlalive">WMLAlive</a>
      <a href="#" onclick="showSection('work')" data-section="work">Work</a>
    </div>
    <div class="nav-group">
      <span class="nav-group-label">More</span>
      <a href="#" onclick="showSection('archive')" data-section="archive">Archive</a>
      <a href="#" onclick="showSection('cv')" data-section="cv">CV</a>
      <a href="#" onclick="showSection('about')" data-section="about">About</a>
    </div>
  </nav>

  <div class="sidebar-bottom">
    <button class="lang-toggle" onclick="toggleLang()">EN / KR</button>
    <div class="sidebar-contact">
      <a href="mailto:suhyouri@gmail.com">suhyouri@gmail.com</a>
      <a href="https://www.instagram.com/suhyouri" target="_blank">Instagram</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</aside>

<main>

  <!-- ── ABOUT ── -->
  <section id="about" class="active">
    <h1>
      Youri Suh
      <span class="kr">서유리</span>
    </h1>
    <div class="divider"></div>
    <p class="statement en">
      I am a Korean-born, Seoul-based visual artist working with play and electronic circuits.
      Since 2023, I have been running a personal project titled <em>WMLAlive</em>
      (What Makes Life Alive), focusing primarily on themes surrounding the body.
      WMLAlive explores the relationship between the body and presence through the question:
      "What makes life alive?" At the boundary between the living and the non-living,
      I ask: on what basis do we consider "that body" to be alive? Or not alive?
      Through the ghostliness of the inanimate, I continue my attempt to speak about
      "the body as evidence of existence" and what it means to be alive.
    </p>
    <p class="statement kr hidden">
      한국 출신으로 서울을 기반으로 활동하는 시각예술가입니다.
      놀이와 전기 회로를 매체로 작업하며, 2023년부터 신체를 중심 주제로 한
      개인 프로젝트 <em>WMLAlive(What Makes Life Alive)</em>를 진행하고 있습니다.
      WMLAlive는 "무엇이 생명을 살아있게 하는가"라는 질문을 통해 신체와 존재의
      관계를 탐구합니다. 살아있음과 살아있지 않음의 경계에서,
      우리는 어떤 근거로 "저 신체"가 살아있다고, 혹은 살아있지 않다고 판단하는가.
      무생물의 유령성을 통해 "존재의 증거로서의 신체"와 살아있다는 것의 의미를
      말하려는 시도를 계속합니다.
    </p>
  </section>

  <!-- ── WMLALIVE ── -->
  <section id="wmlalive">
    <h2 class="section-title">WMLAlive</h2>
    <span class="section-sub">What Makes Life Alive — ongoing since 2023</span>

    <p class="wml-intro en">
      An ongoing project exploring the body, presence, and the question of aliveness.
      WMLAlive emerges from a fascination with the moments we misjudge life—
      what we thought was alive, dead; what we thought was dead, alive.
      The project investigates the criteria and processes behind these judgments.
    </p>
    <p class="wml-intro kr hidden">
      신체, 존재, 그리고 살아있음의 질문을 탐구하는 진행 중인 프로젝트.
      우리가 살아있음을 오판하는 순간들—살아있다고 생각했는데 죽어 있었던 것,
      죽어있다고 생각했는데 살아있었던 것—에 대한 매혹에서 출발합니다.
      이러한 판단의 기준과 과정을 탐구합니다.
    </p>

    <div class="project-card">
      <div class="project-year">2023</div>
      <div>
        <div class="project-title">WMLAlive: The Body as an Island</div>
        <div class="project-meta">Solo Exhibition · spaceuooyoung · Seoul Foundation for Arts and Culture (SFAC)</div>
        <p class="project-desc en">A solo exhibition interrogating the body as an isolated yet porous entity—an island surrounded but never fully reached.</p>
        <p class="project-desc kr hidden">신체를 고립되어 있지만 다공성을 가진 존재로 탐구하는 개인전. spaceuooyoung에서 서울문화재단 지원으로 개최.</p>
        <div class="img-placeholder">image · coming soon</div>
        <a href="https://suhyouri.notion.site/wmlalive" class="project-link" target="_blank">View project →</a>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="project-card">
      <div class="project-year">2025</div>
      <div>
        <div class="project-title">Research on the Walking Methods of Inanimate Objects</div>
        <div class="project-meta">Ongoing Research · Seongnam Cultural Foundation — Young Artist Support Grant</div>
        <p class="project-desc en">An ongoing research project investigating how inanimate objects move—or appear to move—and what that motion implies about presence and aliveness.</p>
        <p class="project-desc kr hidden">무생물이 어떻게 움직이는지를 탐구하는 리서치 프로젝트. 성남문화재단 청년예술가 지원으로 진행 중.</p>
        <div class="img-placeholder">image · coming soon</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ── WORK ── -->
  <section id="work">
    <h2 class="section-title">Work</h2>
    <span class="section-sub">Installation &amp; Electronic Circuits</span>

    <div class="project-card">
      <div class="project-year">2024</div>
      <div>
        <div class="project-title">Circuit Making Memories — PCB Kit</div>
        <div class="project-meta">Gyeonggi Cultural Foundation — Artist Self-Reliance Support</div>
        <p class="project-desc en">A DIY PCB kit exploring memory and electronic circuit as artistic material.</p>
        <p class="project-desc kr hidden">기억과 전자 회로를 예술적 재료로 탐구하는 DIY PCB 키트.</p>
        <div class="img-placeholder">image · coming soon</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="project-card">
      <div class="project-year">2024</div>
      <div>
        <div class="project-title">Super Test Bed Kinetic Lab — Super Rookie</div>
        <div class="project-meta">Arts Management Support Center</div>
        <p class="project-desc en">Selected as Super Rookie for the Kinetic Lab program, exploring kinetic and electronic art practices.</p>
        <p class="project-desc kr hidden">키네틱 랩 프로그램 슈퍼 루키로 선정.</p>
        <div class="img-placeholder">image · coming soon</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="project-card">
      <div class="project-year">2021</div>
      <div>
        <div class="project-title">Circuit Swell</div>
        <div class="project-meta">Research on Electronic Circuit Basics and Modular Synthesis · Arts Council Korea (ARKO)</div>
        <p class="project-desc en">A research project investigating electronic circuit fundamentals and modular synthesis as both medium and subject of artistic practice.</p>
        <p class="project-desc kr hidden">전자 회로 기초와 모듈러 신디사이스를 예술 실천의 매체이자 주제로 탐구. 예술위원회 지원.</p>
        <div class="img-placeholder">image · coming soon</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="project-card">
      <div class="project-year">2020</div>
      <div>
        <div class="project-title">Non-Boundary of Senses: A World in Contact</div>
        <div class="project-meta">Group Exhibition · Sewoon Hall · Korea Creative Content Agency (KOCCA)</div>
        <p class="project-desc en">A group exhibition exploring sensory boundaries and the porous threshold between self and world.</p>
        <p class="project-desc kr hidden">감각의 경계를 탐구하는 그룹 전시. 세운홀, 한국콘텐츠진흥원 주최.</p>
        <div class="img-placeholder">image · coming soon</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ── ARCHIVE ── -->
  <section id="archive">
    <h2 class="section-title">Archive</h2>
    <span class="archive-note">2013 – 2022 · illustration, book, conceptual work, photography</span>

    <div class="archive-filter">
      <button class="filter-btn active" data-filter="all">All</button>
      <button class="filter-btn" data-filter="conceptual">Conceptual</button>
      <button class="filter-btn" data-filter="book">Book</button>
      <button class="filter-btn" data-filter="illustration">Illustration</button>
      <button class="filter-btn" data-filter="photo">Photo</button>
    </div>

